  <li>
    <p><strong>AA and KK: how to play on the Flop</strong></p>

    <ul>
      <li>I play a Pair of Aces or Kings very cautiously from an early position when thereâ€™s three cards thatâ€™ll make a Straight or a Flush on the Flop. This is especially true if there are two or more people in the pot with me. The guys that called behind me are liable to have anything. In that position, theyâ€™ve either got a hand that could break me â€¦ or Iâ€™ll win a very small pot if I bet. So, in an early position, a bell rings (reminding me not to bet) when I see three to a Straight or Flush on the Flop when Iâ€™ve got Aces or King in the pocket.
