    <ol>
      <li>Youâ€™ll win a small pot or</li>
      <li>Youâ€™ll lose a big pot</li>
    </ol>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>You should always remember that the Flop is practically the whole game in Hold â€˜em. Thatâ€™s where your major decisions will be made. The play on Fourth St. and Fifth St. is pretty basic</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>If you think youâ€™re beat, naturally, you check it â€¦ and if you think your opponentâ€™s drawing â€¦ you bet. Thatâ€™s the whole thing</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>On the end (Fifth St.), if it looks like your opponent has missed his hand â€¦
