      </li>
      <li>The reason why you can make more money with an AK than with two Aces (or Kings) is because itâ€™s a drawing type of hand as opposed to a made hand. I mean, you donâ€™t have anything with an AK unless you flop something. So you can get away from it real easy. Youâ€™re not tied on to it like you might be with a Pair of Aces (or Kings). And thatâ€™s why youâ€™ll lose less money with it. Another reason why you can make more and lose less with AK than with the very big Pairs is because when you have AK and you pair the Ace or King on the Flop â€¦ itâ€™s much harder for your opponent to make his hand if heâ€™s playing something like two connecting cards. For example, if someoneâ€™s playing a 7 6 and the Board comes A 9 8, he hasnâ€™t made anything yetâ€¦because when you pair one of your hole cards there can be only two cards thatâ€™ll help him. But, if you had two Aces in the pocket â€¦ the Board could come 9 8 5 or any three cards that could help his hand (such as a Pair and a draw). That one extra card considerably improves his chances of cracking your Aces</li>
