  <li><strong>AK: how to play on Fourth and Fifth</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>The way youâ€™d play A K on Fourth and Fifth Sts. (if you made a Pair on the Flop) is almost the same way youâ€™d play a Pair of Aces or Kings in the pocket. If you think your opponent made the hand he was drawing at â€¦ you check. If you donâ€™t think he made it â€¦ you bet. The only exception would be when you thought you had a man out kicked.</li>
