  <li><strong>Playing JJ, 10 10, 99</strong>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>I also have a breaking-point that I use in my play with a Pair of Jacks, Tens and Nines. I mentally segregate them from the other small Pairs and I play them a little stronger than the others. I do it simply because theyâ€™re bigger Pairs and itâ€™s pretty easy for three Rags to fall. When that happens â€¦ youâ€™ll have an overpair. But, if youâ€™ve got two Fives or two Sixes, itâ€™s hard for a Turn to come without there being at least one overcard. And, with an overcard out there, your hand is kind of dead so you donâ€™t want to get too much money involved. Progressively, then, each Pair is a little bit better than the others â€¦ but I play them all as if they were a small Pair</p>
